CAN PIONEERING surgery help delay the menopause and how will it impact women's lives? And, Clara Vu, of Veo Robotics, explains some of the challenges of designing “cobots”, robots that work collaboratively with humans on manufacturing tasks. Also, should people have the right to choose to know if they are a carrier of a hereditary genetic disease? Alok Jha hosts. Runtime: 20 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn